BRAZIL DAYBOOK: OGX Conference Call, Central Bank Weekly Survey

-- B y   R o b i n   S t r i n g e r
-- 
2011-05-09T03:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-09/brazil-daybook-ogx-conference-call-central-bank-weekly-survey.html
Executives of OGX Petroleo & Gas
Participacoes SA, the  oil company  controlled by billionaire  Eike
Batista , discuss the company’s first-quarter results in a
conference call with investors and analysts at 9:00 a.m. OGX
posted a loss of 33.9 million reais for the period, from a
profit of 56.9 million reais a year earlier, the company said
May 6 after the markets close.  GOVERNMENT:
*President Dilma Rousseff meets Institutional Affairs Minister
Luiz Sergio Oliveira in Brasilia at 11 a.m.
*Finance Minister  Guido Mantega  has internal meetings in
Brasilia.
*Central bank president Alexandre Tombini participates of a
meeting of central bankers in Basel, Switzerland.  WHAT TO WATCH:
* Brazil ’s efforts to slow inflation won’t keep the nation’s
economy from growing at a “sustainable” pace, Finance Minister
Guido Mantega said in a video interview posted on the website of
Folha de S.Paulo on May 7.
*Apimec Rio hosts a meeting with Embraer executives in  Rio de
Janeiro  at 5:30 p.m.
*Heineken considering an offer for Primo Schincariol Industria
de Cervejas (845928Z BZ), according to people familiar with the
matter
*International Consolidated Airlines Group SA may bid for TAP
SGPS SA,  Portugal ’s state-owned airline, the Sunday Times
reported yesterday, without saying where it got the information.
Deutsche Lufthansa AG and an alliance between Brazilian airline
TAM SA and Chile’s LAN Airlines SA may also bid, the newspaper
said.  ECONOMY:
*FGV weekly consumer price index IPC-S 8:00 a.m.
*FGV broad inflation index IGP-DI at 8:00 a.m.
*Central bank weekly economists survey at 8:30 a.m.
*Weekly trade balance at 11:00 a.m.  EARNINGS:
*Hypermarcas (HYPE3 BS) reports first-quarter results.  EQUITIES:
*Vale (VALE5 BZ) will double Mozambique investment to $4 billion
*OGX (OGXP3 BZ) posted a first-quarter loss of 33.9 million
reais
*Petroleo Brasileiro will boost output to produce 15 percent of
Brazil’s ethanol output in the next three to four years
*Itau (ITUB4 BZ) ordered to pay damages in Madoff case, Folha
reported
*PDG Realty SA Empreendimentos & Participacoes climbed the most
in four months on May 6  MARKETS
*The Bovespa index rose 1.6 percent to 64,417.33.
*The real strengthened 0.4 percent to 1.6150 per dollar.  To contact the reporter on this story:
